# =============================================================================
# .clinerules - Generative UI Deployment & Monitoring Standards
# Angular + UI5 Webcomponents + Nginx Gateway Configuration
# =============================================================================

# This file defines rules and standards for the generativeUI stack to prevent
# and detect deployment issues like blank pages, asset loading failures, and
# compression problems. These rules are derived from the April 2026 blank page
# incident investigation at https://suite-gateway.c-054c570.kyma.ondemand.com/ui5/
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# KNOWN ISSUE REGISTRY
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## KI-001: i18n Path Resolution Under Subpath

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Issue ID | KI-001 |
| Status | RESOLVED (April 2026) |
| Severity | P0 - Critical (blank page) |
| Root Cause | fetchI18n() using absolute paths (/assets/i18n/...) that 404 under /ui5/ subpath |

**Symptoms:**
- 404 errors for `/assets/i18n/messages_en` when app served under `/ui5/`
- App bootstraps but fails to render due to missing translations
- Network tab shows successful HTML/JS loads but failed i18n requests

**Resolution:**
```typescript
// CORRECT: Read base href from DOM and construct paths dynamically
const baseHref = document.querySelector('base')?.getAttribute('href') || '/';
const i18nPath = `${baseHref}assets/i18n/messages_${locale}`;

// INCORRECT: Absolute paths that fail under subpath routing
const i18nPath = `/assets/i18n/messages_${locale}`;
```

**Prevention Rules:**
1. ALL asset paths MUST be relative or read from `<base href>`
2. NEVER hardcode absolute paths starting with `/` for frontend assets
3. Angular apps MUST use `APP_BASE_HREF` token when constructing URLs

---

## KI-002: Gzip Compression Disabled by sub_filter

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Issue ID | KI-002 |
| Status | RESOLVED (April 2026) |
| Severity | P1 - High (performance degradation, perceived blank page) |
| Root Cause | proxy_set_header Accept-Encoding "" required for sub_filter disables upstream gzip |

**Symptoms:**
- vendor.js delivered as 1.7 MB uncompressed (vs ~400KB gzipped)
- First paint takes 10-30 seconds on slow connections
- Browser appears to show blank page during extended download
- sub_filter rewrites work correctly but at cost of compression

**Technical Explanation:**
```nginx
# The problem: sub_filter requires uncompressed content to perform string replacement
location /ui5/ {
    proxy_set_header Accept-Encoding "";  # <-- This disables upstream gzip
    sub_filter '<base href="/">' '<base href="/ui5/">';  # <-- sub_filter needs raw text
    # Result: All responses from ui5-web arrive uncompressed
}
```

**Mitigation (Current):**
1. Serve pre-compressed .gz files from nginx with gzip_static module
2. Gateway must NOT strip Accept-Encoding for static assets after sub_filter processing

**Full Fix (TODO):**
```dockerfile
# In Dockerfile.suite-web, after build step:
RUN find /workspace/dist/apps/workspace -type f \( -name "*.js" -o -name "*.css" -o -name "*.html" -o -name "*.json" \) -exec gzip -9 -k {} \;
```

```nginx
# In nginx-suite-web.conf:
gzip_static on;
gzip_vary on;
```

---

## KI-003: Webpack publicPath Misconfiguration

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Issue ID | KI-003 |
| Status | RESOLVED |
| Severity | P0 - Critical (blank page) |
| Root Cause | Webpack publicPath must be "" (empty) when Angular uses `<base href>` |

**Symptoms:**
- Lazy-loaded chunks fail to load
- CSS/fonts load from wrong path
- Console shows 404 for chunk files

**Verification:**
```bash
# Check publicPath in bundled main.js
grep -o 'publicPath:"[^"]*"' dist/apps/workspace/main.js
# Expected: publicPath:""
# Bad: publicPath:"/ui5/" or publicPath:"/"
```

**Build Command (Correct):**
```bash
# Angular CLI handles publicPath automatically when --base-href is set
yarn nx build workspace --configuration=production --base-href /ui5/
```

---

## KI-004: JS Runtime Errors During Bootstrap

| Attribute | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Issue ID | KI-004 |
| Status | MONITORING |
| Severity | P0 - Critical (blank page) |
| Root Cause | Various - requires browser DevTools to diagnose |

**Symptoms:**
- HTML loads, JS bundles load (200 OK), but page remains blank
- API calls may still fire (Angular bootstraps partially)
- No visual rendering occurs

**Diagnostic Checklist:**
1. Open DevTools Console - check for red errors
2. Check Network tab - all JS/CSS should be 200
3. Check for `requireRealBackends` config - may block rendering if APIs unreachable
4. Check for UI5 theme initialization errors
5. Check for Angular zone.js errors

**Common Fixes:**
```typescript
// If requireRealBackends causes blocking:
environment.requireRealBackends = false; // For development/testing

// If APP_INITIALIZER fails:
// Wrap in try-catch with fallback behavior
```

