# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NGINX CONFIGURATION STANDARDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Gateway nginx.conf.template Rules

1. **sub_filter Blocks Must Include Compression Handling:**
```nginx
location /ui5/ {
    proxy_pass http://ui5_web/;
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    
    # Required for sub_filter to work on response body
    proxy_set_header Accept-Encoding "";
    
    sub_filter_types text/html;
    sub_filter_once off;
    sub_filter '<base href="/">' '<base href="/ui5/">';
    sub_filter 'href="/' 'href="/ui5/';
    sub_filter 'src="/' 'src="/ui5/';
    
    # NOTE: Accept-Encoding "" means upstream cannot send gzip
    # Mitigation: ui5-web MUST serve pre-gzipped assets via gzip_static
}
```

2. **Static Asset Locations Should NOT Use sub_filter:**
```nginx
# For pre-compressed static assets (if serving directly from gateway)
location ~* \.(js|css|woff2?|ttf|ico|svg|png|jpg|jpeg|gif)$ {
    gzip_static on;
    expires 1y;
    add_header Cache-Control "public, immutable";
}
```

## UI5-Web nginx-suite-web.conf Rules

1. **Enable gzip_static for pre-compressed files:**
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name _;
    root /usr/share/nginx/html;
    index index.html;
    
    # Enable serving pre-compressed .gz files
    gzip_static on;
    gzip_vary on;
    
    # Fallback gzip for non-pre-compressed content
    gzip on;
    gzip_types text/plain text/css application/json application/javascript text/xml application/xml;
    gzip_min_length 1000;
    
    location = /health {
        default_type application/json;
        return 200 '{"status":"ok","service":"ui5-web"}';
    }
    
    location /ui5/ {
        alias /usr/share/nginx/html/;
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }
    
    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
    }
}
```

