# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MONITORING & ALERTING RULES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Synthetic Monitoring (Recommended)

Set up automated checks that run every 5 minutes:

```yaml
# monitoring/synthetic-checks.yaml
checks:
  - name: ui5-page-loads
    url: ${GATEWAY_URL}/ui5/
    assertions:
      - type: responseTime
        operator: lessThan
        value: 5000
      - type: statusCode
        operator: equals
        value: 200
      - type: body
        operator: contains
        value: '<base href="/ui5/">'
    
  - name: ui5-vendor-js
    url: ${GATEWAY_URL}/ui5/vendor.js
    headers:
      Accept-Encoding: gzip
    assertions:
      - type: statusCode
        operator: equals
        value: 200
      - type: header
        name: content-encoding
        operator: equals
        value: gzip
      - type: responseTime
        operator: lessThan
        value: 3000

  - name: ui5-api-health
    url: ${GATEWAY_URL}/api/v1/ui5/openai/health
    assertions:
      - type: statusCode
        operator: equals
        value: 200
      - type: responseTime
        operator: lessThan
        value: 1000
```

## Alert Thresholds

| Metric | Warning | Critical | Action |
|--------|---------|----------|--------|
| Page load time | > 5s | > 15s | Check compression, CDN |
| vendor.js size (uncompressed) | > 2MB | > 3MB | Bundle audit, tree shaking |
| i18n 404 rate | > 1% | > 5% | Check path configuration |
| JS error rate | > 1% | > 5% | Check console logs |
| API health check failure | 1 | 3 consecutive | Check backend pods |

